messages.content: What is the purpose of the comfyui-ultralytics-yolo node?
The comfyui-ultralytics-yolo node integrates the YOLO-WORLD models from Ultralytics into ComfyUI for object detection and segmentation tasks.
Where can I seek help for the comfyui-ultralytics-yolo node?
You can seek help for the comfyui-ultralytics-yolo node on the Mixlab nodes Discord server: https://discord.gg/cXs9vZSqeK
What is a recommended resource for additional ComfyUI nodes?
The mixlab-nodes repository on GitHub (https://github.com/shadowcz007/comfyui-mixlab-nodes) is a recommended resource for additional ComfyUI nodes.
Where can I find documentation for YOLO-WORLD models?
Documentation for YOLO-WORLD models can be found at: https://docs.ultralytics.com/zh/models/yolo-world/
Where should the YOLO-WORLD models be placed within the ComfyUI directory structure?
The YOLO-WORLD models should be placed in the ComfyUI/models/ultralytics directory.
Where can I download the YOLO-WORLD models?
You can download the YOLO-WORLD models from the Ultralytics assets releases page on GitHub: https://github.com/ultralytics/assets/releases/
What tasks and operating modes are supported by YOLO-WORLD models?

The supported tasks and operating modes for YOLO-WORLD models can be found in the documentation at: https://docs.ultralytics.com/zh/models/yolo-world/#available-models-supported-tasks-and-operating-modes
